/// description:
/// <br>
/// <br>
/// The &nbsp; <a class="rosetta__link--wiki" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sutherland-Hodgman clipping algorithm" title="wp: Sutherland-Hodgman clipping algorithm">Sutherland-Hodgman clipping algorithm</a> &nbsp; finds the polygon that is the intersection between an arbitrary polygon (the “subject polygon”) and a convex polygon (the “clip polygon”). 
/// <br>
/// It is used in computer graphics (especially 2D graphics) to reduce the complexity of a scene being displayed by eliminating parts of a polygon that do not need to be displayed.
/// <br>
